snippet.textDisplay: Glad to see you finally added this masterpiece to your VGM collection. MGS4 is an amazing game, the shitty love stories of it not withstanding. It needed way more gameplay in Act 3 and 5, but it's still fantastic. The best gameplay in the series, because it removes the MGS3 healing system that requires you to go through the menu too much, adds octocamo and crouch walking, and has the rations and other stuff from MGS2.

snippet.textDisplay: Kojima not being involved with Metal Gear Solid anymore is the end of the golden era of the franchise. There are some game series that simply cannot be the same without their creators, I can also think of Silent Hill/Team Silent or Final Fantasy/Sakaguchi. It's just not the same anymore. Metal Gear Survive is obviously a side-game and I'm wondering if Konami will ever bother trying to make a real entry. You had a good run Snake.
snippet.textOriginal: Kojima not being involved with Metal Gear Solid anymore is the end of the golden era of the franchise. There are some game series that simply cannot be the same without their creators, I can also think of Silent Hill/Team Silent or Final Fantasy/Sakaguchi. It's just not the same anymore. Metal Gear Survive is obviously a side-game and I'm wondering if Konami will ever bother trying to make a real entry. You had a good run Snake.

snippet.textDisplay:
All Konami needs is passion. If the developers that Kojima left behind at the company can muster any genuine interest and love for the series then we might actually see some amazing results. 

I mean, look at Kirby. The series creator, Masahiro Sakurai, has little to no involvement with most of the titles and yet it managed to maintain its quality standards and far surpass it in some cases.
